jhelp.util.list
Class SortedArray<TYPE>

java.lang.Object
  jhelp.util.list.SortedArray<TYPE>
Type Parameters:
TYPE - Type of stored elements
public final class SortedArray<TYPE>
extends java.lang.Object

Array of sorted element.
The sort is "natural order" (Only possible for Comparable elements) or as indicates by a Comparator.
The sort can be unique, that is to say if try to add an element and exists an other inside array that compare equals, in unique mode, the element is not add.
The adding, remove are in O(n * LN(n)). The search is in O(LN(n)).

Author:
JHelp
